            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>stock</strong>, your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong> to the pan with your orzo</p><p>Add the juice of<strong> half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s] </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Stir the orzo occasionally to stop it from sticking</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
