            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>When the orzo has 6 min left, return the reserved pan to a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, sprinkle in your <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano,</strong> then add the <strong>seasoned salmon fillet[s] </strong>and cook for 9-10 min, turning once halfway, or until cooked through – this is your <strong>oregano salmon</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
