            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the orzo is ready, remove it from the heat and stir through the<strong> chopped dill </strong>with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and a generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until warmed through – this is your <strong>prasorizo-style dill orzo</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p><p>Discard the<strong> bay leaf[ves]</strong></p>",
